nodes.context_tip:
Welcome to Hypersomnia!
Press {MOVE_FORWARD}, {MOVE_BACKWARD}, {MOVE_LEFT}, {MOVE_RIGHT} to move around.
Go up!
Move your mouse to look around.

Hold {SPRINT} to sprint.
Quickly run over the red tiles!

Press {DASH} to dash.
Dash over the red floors!

Let us begin!
Enter the yellow portal.

Running costs Stamina.
Walk or stand still to regenerate faster.

Hold {WALK_SILENTLY} to walk silently.
Enemies won't hear your footsteps.
Walk over the red floor!

Time to shoot things up.
Pick up the weapon on the floor.
Pick up magazines and press {RELOAD} to reload.

Press {SHOOT} to shoot.
Kill the Resistance soldier to continue.
Watch your ammo! You can always restart this level.

Press {TOGGLE_WEAPON_LASER} to toggle laser.
Dashed lines indicate a physical obstacle.

Enemies are invisible behind obstacles.
Bullets can still penetrate and kill - depending on the gun.

Press {HOLSTER} to hide your gun.
You will fit in tight corridors.

Press {LAST_USED_WEAPON} to pull your gun back.
{LAST_USED_WEAPON} now quickly switches between the gun and free hands.

Whenever you're stuck, press Escape.
Then click "Restart from last checkpoint".

Press {DROP} to drop your weapon.
This frees inventory space.

Tip: double-tapping {RELOAD} reloads faster.
This drops the mag to the ground. You can pick it up later!

Tip: try shooting while reloading!
This will fire the bullet left in the chamber.
You can dual-wield any two weapons.

Hold two numbers to dual-wield. E.g. {HOTBAR_0} and {HOTBAR_1}.
Try killing both enemies at the same time.

Hold {HOTBAR_0} and {HOTBAR_1} to dual wield Deagles.
Use their massive recoil to quickly jump over the red floor.

You move really slow when dual-wielding.
However, you can compensate with kickback!

Aim in the opposite direction (down).
Hold {SPRINT} and {MOVE_FORWARD} while shooting both Deagles.
Good job!
{RELOAD} will automatically reload both weapons.

Your weapons show on the hotbar.
Press a corresponding number ({HOTBAR_0} or {HOTBAR_1}) to pull one out.

Tip: press the same number (e.g. {HOTBAR_0}) several times in a row.
This toggles between right-handed and left-handed stance!

This means you can move extremely fast,
even with a very heavy weapon!

Tip: gun recoil is the same every time.
You can learn the pattern!

Shoot the glassy surface from an angle.
Kill 4 enemies camping behind the corners.

Bullets can bounce against walls!
Glass is the easiest to ricochet off.

ALL surfaces can bounce bullets.
Wood is the hardest, but absolutely possible!
Good job!
Pressing {HOLSTER} won't free your hands anymore...

Inventory space is limited.
Try picking up both sniper rifles.

This is bad if you want to run fast.
You also won't fit inside tight corridors.

This is when having a Backpack is useful.
Pick it up.

Now just press {HOLSTER} and walk through the corridor.
You must face to the side.

It's time for the Deagle trick..
..but with two Awkas instead.
Hold {HOTBAR_0} and {HOTBAR_1} to dual-wield.

Knives can be thrown quickly.
Aim at the enemy and spam {THROW_KNIFE}.

You can use the laser ({TOGGLE_WEAPON_LASER}) with knives too.
Aim for headshots, especially with the strong attack.

Press {SHOOT} for a fast, weak attack.
Press {SHOOT_SECONDARY} for a strong, slow attack.

Time to chop things up.
Pick up the red knife.

The faster you are, the harder you hit.
Attack with {SHOOT_SECONDARY} while sprinting full speed.

You can throw two knives at once!
Simply {THROW_TWO_KNIVES}.

For better aim, dual-wield knives by holding {HOTBAR_0} and {HOTBAR_1}.
Then {THROW_KNIFE} or {THROW_TWO_KNIVES}.

Press strong attack while running.
({SPRINT} + {MOVE_FORWARD}, then {SHOOT_SECONDARY})

You can toss knives in ANY situation. Even while reloading a gun!
Try it out! {THROW_KNIFE} or {THROW_TWO_KNIVES}. This can save your life.

Will you manage?
Or will you perish?

Assault Rattle has a cool feature.
Its strong attack lets you jump!
Good job!
Thrown knives can bounce against walls and kill enemies.

These enemies can only be killed with headshots. Use Baka47.
Can you kill two in one shot? What about three?

Headshots deal 3x damage.
They're based on accuracy. They are not random.
Use {LAST_USED_WEAPON} to quickly switch to the last used gun.

So whenever you can, always free your hands with {HOLSTER}.
Then tap {LAST_USED_WEAPON} to alternate between combat and fast movement!
Your speed depends only on what's in your hands.

Time to blow things up.
But first let's wear some protection.

Press {SHOOT} to throw. Hold to cook it (watch out!).
Use {TOGGLE_WEAPON_LASER} to see what you can throw over.
Press {SHOOT_SECONDARY} to throw a grenade close.

There are other kinds of grenades.
PED (blue ones) instantly destroy armor and PE.

Flashbangs blind and deafen nearby enemies.
Test it on yourself with {SHOOT_SECONDARY}.

Yellow ones are the cheapest - they only drain stamina and throw enemies away.
They also force gun ignition  - good for trolling rocket launcher users.

Just like knives, you can toss grenades in any situation -
even while shooting or reloading!

{THROW_FORCE_GRENADE} quickly tosses a Force Grenade.
{THROW_PED_GRENADE} tosses PED grenades.
{THROW_FLASHBANG} tosses Flashbangs.
Tip: To reach around corners, bounce grenades against walls.

When playing Resistance, you must detonate the bomb to win.
If you don't plant it within the time limit, you lose the round.

Often, there is more than one bombsite - named A, B and C.
Detonating any single one wins the round for Resistance.
The bomb could end up on the ground due to your teammate dying.

First, enter the bombsite - it's always marked with red lines.
It is usually defended by Metropolis players.

Quick! Grab the Defuse kit.
You will defuse TWICE as fast!
Quick! Retake the bombsite and defuse the bomb!
Kill the terrorists first!
Another bomb's already ticking!
You did well! Good job!

When you kill the enemy carrying the bomb,
you can steal it and run away! Try it!
Avoid the explosion! Take cover!

Guess what - you can toss knives and nades while planting!
Try it out!

Electric Armor makes PE absorb all damage.
It is effectively a second HP bar.

Cons? You walk a little slower and glow in the dark.
Okay, let's pick up some grenades!

Press {SPECIAL_ACTION_BUTTON_1} to cast Haste.
You will run faster for a while.

You can cast Spells.
They consume PE (Personal Electricity).
{SPECIAL_ACTION_BUTTON_6} will restore your Health.

Just like HP, PE slowly regenerates.
Without enough PE, spells appear grayed out.
{SPECIAL_ACTION_BUTTON_5} will restore your Stamina.

Press {SPECIAL_ACTION_BUTTON_3} to launch three massive explosions.
These cannot hurt you.

You can counter Spell users with Blunaz.
It instantly drains victim's PE - but is otherwise useless.

Press {SPECIAL_ACTION_BUTTON_4} to cast three magic missiles.
Watch out, you can die from the explosion!

Let's try some offensive spells.
In the Tutorial, they won't consume PE.
Press {SPECIAL_ACTION_BUTTON_2} for a small, instant explosion.

It is a great alternative to PED grenades.
Try it on yourself!
Surfing with portals is possible!

Let's try the simplest track.
Simply hold {MOVE_FORWARD} until you fly to the other side.

Awesome!
Let's try something harder.

You'll have to make a quick turn to the right.
Hold {MOVE_FORWARD} until you hit the second portal. Then press and hold {MOVE_RIGHT}.

Good job!
Let's get serious now.

Bullet trajectory ({TOGGLE_WEAPON_LASER}) must cross the enemy's head.
It's possible to headshot even from the side!
Good job!
This way, enemies can die without ever seeing you!
Hold {MOVE_FORWARD} and then press {DASH}.

Hold {MOVE_RIGHT} and then press {DASH}.
Dash direction is the same as movement direction.

Tip: Use dash to boost ({DASH}). It prolongs airborne time.
Don't use Sprint ({SPRINT}). It is useless when flying.

This track requires you to make a full circle.
Good luck.

Congratulations!
You're now a certified surfer!

The left portal will take you to the Main menu.
Or, you can go to Shooting range to test all 20+ weapons.

You have completed the Tutorial!
Thank you for playing!

Not enough surfing?
How about a really hardcore trial?
Now there is no turning back.
CONGRATULATIONS!

Aim in the opposite direction (down).
Hold {SPRINT} and {MOVE_FORWARD} while shooting both Awkas.

Tip: there are 3 enemies,
each hiding behind a crate.
